input_str: Fighting has always been a polarizing issue in society, and has increasingly become controversial in hockey as well, the one major American sport where a fight is not accompanied by a significant suspension. In life outside of sports, there are crowds that view fighting as a perfectly acceptable way to handle a disagreement or send a message, while others view it as cruel and barbaric. Similarly, in the hockey community there are people who view fighting as a necessary part of the game, while others view it as an outdated practice that no longer has a place in today
